  "prompt": "Do the prime minister of our country require visa to visit any country?",
  "response": "Yes, the Prime Minister of a country typically requires a visa to visit other countries, just like any other individual. However, the process may vary depending on the country they are visiting and diplomatic agreements in place. In many instances, heads of state or government might have specific privileges or exemptions, such as visa-free entry or expedited processing, due to their official status. It's also common for official trips to be coordinated through diplomatic channels, which can facilitate travel arrangements.",
